  "prompt": "What does a US green card holder need to travel to Canada?",
  "response": "To travel to Canada, a U.S. green card holder typically needs:\n\n1. A valid passport from their country of citizenship\n\n2. A valid permanent resident card (green card)\n\n3. An Electronic Travel Authorization (eTA), which can be obtained online before traveling\n\nIf the green card holder is not a citizen of a visa-exempt country, they may also need a valid visitor visa (temporary resident visa) in addition to the eTA.\n\nIt's recommended to check the current entry requirements with the Canadian government or a Canadian embassy before traveling, as regulations can change.",
